\name{multiomics.workflow}
\alias{multiomics.workflow}
\title{Multi-omics RNA/Proteomics workflow for VisomX}
\usage{
multiomics.workflow(
  rna_se,
  prot_se,
  sample_covariates = NULL,
  match_samples = c("intersection", "none"),
  rna_args = list(),
  prot_args = list(),
  prot_covariate = TRUE,
  prot_covariate_options = list(),
  quiet = FALSE
)
}
\arguments{
  \item{rna_se}{A \code{SummarizedExperiment} containing RNA-seq counts prepared for \code{rna.workflow()}.}
  \item{prot_se}{A \code{SummarizedExperiment} containing proteomics intensities prepared for \code{prot.workflow()}.}
  \item{sample_covariates}{Optional \code{data.frame} of sample-level covariates (rownames must correspond to sample identifiers). Numeric columns are used for covariate correlation analyses.}
  \item{match_samples}{Either \code{"intersection"} (default) to restrict both assays and covariates to the overlapping sample names, or \code{"none"} to run the workflows on the supplied objects without enforcing overlap.}
  \item{rna_args}{Named list of additional arguments forwarded to \code{rna.workflow()}. Entries override defaults set by \code{multiomics.workflow()}.}
  \item{prot_args}{Named list of additional arguments forwarded to \code{prot.workflow()}.}
  \item{prot_covariate}{Logical (default \code{TRUE}); if \code{TRUE} and covariates are provided they are forwarded to \code{prot.workflow()} so that protein/pathway correlation analyses are executed.}
  \item{prot_covariate_options}{Named list whose entries override the corresponding arguments in \code{prot.workflow()} (e.g. \code{correlate_proteins}, \code{correlate_pathways}, \code{pathway_min_genes}, \code{correlation_method}, \code{correlation_p_adjust}, \code{correlation_var_filter}, \code{correlation_min_sd}, \code{correlation_low_n}, \code{gsea_covariates}).}
  \item{quiet}{Logical; passed through to \code{rna.workflow()} when not already supplied via \code{rna_args}.}
}
\value{
A list containing the RNA and proteomics workflow outputs enriched with shared metadata. The top-level entries include \code{rna}, \code{proteomics}, \code{samples}, \code{sample_covariates}, \code{shared_contrasts}, and \code{metadata}.
}
\description{
\code{multiomics.workflow()} coordinates the existing RNA sequencing (\code{rna.workflow}) and proteomics (\code{prot.workflow}) pipelines, optionally aligning samples, sharing sample-level covariates, and augmenting the proteomics results with the covariate correlation analyses that were previously only available for RNA data.
}
\details{
The helper makes it easy to run both assays side-by-side and collect shared metadata such as overlapping samples, contrasts, and proteomics covariate associations. Proteomics covariate correlations are appended to the returned objects when requested.
}
